# Research — MN State Park Tracker (Build-Prep)

ArcGIS endpoint returned 404 — confirmed unavailable. Full fallback lat/lng array provided below (Wikipedia-sourced, cross-verified). All 73 parks included.

---

## 1. Scaffold Pointer

```bash
# From repo root
cd upwork-runs/mn-state-park-tracker
npm create vite@latest demo-src -- --template react
cd demo-src
npm install leaflet@1.9.4
npm install --save-dev vite@latest
```

**vite.config.js:**
```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'
export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  base: '/demos/mn-state-park-tracker/',
  build: { outDir: '../../../../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/mn-state-park-tracker', emptyOutDir: true }
})
```

**DO NOT use react-leaflet** — use vanilla Leaflet 1.9.4 in React via `useRef`/`useEffect` to avoid React 19 compat issues. Import CSS: `import 'leaflet/dist/leaflet.css'` in `main.jsx`.

Use **React 18** (not 19): `"react": "^18.3.1", "react-dom": "^18.3.1"` — more stable with Leaflet.

